attributes.name: Mediastinum
phrases:
Port-A-Cath tip and right IJ line terminate in
 the lower SVC and are unchanged.

The
 NG tube is located above the diaphragm; it loops around in mid mediastinum;
 the tip points superiorly and projects over the anterior second rib; position
 is unchanged.

Widening of the mediastinum appears more marked but this
 difference may be projectional given patient rotation; this likely represents
 post-surgical changes.

IMPRESSION:  
 1.  NGT in unchanged position; interval removal of ETT; other lines unchanged.

3.  Apparent increase in mediastinal widening may be projectional and can be
 reassessed at next chest radiograph.
